    dc:date "2008" ;
    dc:title "A preliminary revision of the Synalpheus paraneptunus Coutière, 1909 species complex (Crustacea: Decapoda: Alpheidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184606>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184607>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184610>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184611> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184606>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Synalpheus bocas n. sp., paratype, male from Bocas del Toro, Panama (USNM 1116692): A, frontal region, dorsal view; B, same, lateral view; C, third maxilliped, tip of ultimate segment, lateral view; D, second pereiopod, lateral view; E, third pereiopod, lateral view; F, abdomen, lateral view; G, telson and uropods, dorsal view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm (A – E, G), 1 mm (F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184606/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184607>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Synalpheus bocas n. sp., paratype, male from Bocas del Toro, Panama (USNM 1116692) [A – E]; paratype, male (USNM 1116690) [F]: A, major cheliped, lateral view; B, same, chela, mesial view; C, same, distal portion with opened fingers, lateral view; D, minor cheliped, lateral view; E, same, chela with opened fingers, mesial view, F, minor chela of young male with opened fingers, dorsolateral aspect. Scale bar: 0.5 mm (C – F), 1 mm (A, B)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184607/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184610>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Life habitus and colour patterns. Synalpheus duffyi n. sp., Isla Grande, Panama [A, B]: A, larger queen and two smaller non-breeding colony members from the same colony, dorsal view; B, queen with embryos, lateral view. Synalpheus brevidactylus n. sp., Isla Grande, Panama [C, D]: C, breeding female and male (mated pair), dorsal view; D, breeding female, lateral view. Synalpheus bocas n. sp., Bocas del Toro, Panama [E – H]: E, male, dorsal view; F, breeding female; G, H, another breeding female, lateral and dorsal views on different backgrounds. Synalpheus belizensis n. sp., Carrie Bow Cay, Belize [I]: I, breeding female, dorsal view. Scale bars: ~ 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184610/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184611>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Sponge hosts of some species from the Synalpheus paraneptunus Coutière, 1909 species complex: A, several members of a colony of Synalpheus duffyi n. sp. in their host sponge, possibly Neopetrosia subtriangularis, Isla Grande, Panama; B, same, close-up of a non-breeding colony member; C, Xestospongia rosariensis, main host of Synalpheus bocas n. sp., Bocas del Toro, Panama; D, same, longitudinal section showing details of canals; E, Xestospongia sp., occasional host of S. bocas n. sp., Bocas del Toro, Panama. Scale bars: ~ 3 mm (A, B), ~ 5 cm (C – E)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184611/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

